                <h1>Ruby Bridges: A Symbol of Courage in the Civil Rights Movement</h1>
                <p>Ruby Bridges, a courageous civil rights activist, made history in 1960 at just six years old when she became the first African American child to integrate an all-white elementary school in Louisiana. Facing immense hostility, her steadfast spirit became a symbol of bravery and hope during the civil rights movement, inspiring generations toward equality.</p>
